@*
    The object-detail drawer (O4/A5). objectDrawer (app.js) composes overlayFocus: it holds .fb-rail and
    .fb-stage inert while open, moves focus to the dialog panel, and restores it on close. The root sits
    outside its own inert list (it is a fourth .fb-app sibling), so the dialog stays reachable while the
    rest of the shell is inert. Escape closes only this overlay (overlayEscape stops the event) and the
    scrim click closes it. The panel is inert while closed, so its cloned controls are out of the tab
    order until it opens. The content slot is filled by cloning the opener row's server-rendered anatomy
    template - no fetch, no client-built markup.
*@
<div class="fb-ddialog" x-data="objectDrawer" x-cloak
     :class="{ 'is-open': $store.drawer.open }"
     @@keydown.escape="overlayEscape($event)">
    <div class="fb-dscrim" @@click="close()"></div>
    <div class="fb-drawer" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="fb-detail-title"
         tabindex="-1" :inert="!$store.drawer.open || null">
        <button type="button" class="fb-xbtn" aria-label="Close" @@click="close()">Close</button>
        <div class="fb-dcontent" x-ref="content"></div>
    </div>
</div>
